Proper segregation of waste;
The incessant utilization of MRF to minimize the volume of wastes to be transported for disposal;
The recording of waste received and its disposal.

We recommended that the Municipal Government plan and prepare the DRRM Implementing Plan as a ready reference and tool for the preparation of future calamities and disasters. The DRRM Implementing Plan to be prepared shall include among others, the following:

mechanism for the timely delivery of relief goods (food and medical supplies) to the victims such as:

assessment on the extent of damage, and needs and numbers of victims;
procurement and repacking of relief goods;
shipment/transporting of relief goods;
manner of distribution to victims;

rules and procedures (protocols) on the:

mobilization of fund resources;
organization of emergency group of responders, rescue teams or community service brigades;
activation of disaster command centers;
installation/activation of area-wide early warning system;
designation of evacuation centers and provision for temporary shelters;
deployment of personnel trained in food handling/relief distribution and medical and rescue teams;
communication links with concerned government agencies and volunteer groups;

information dissemination on disaster awareness and preparedness;
roles and responsibilities of the implementing government agencies/offices and Civil Society Organizations (CSOs);
manner of coordination between, among and within the implementing agencies; and
periodic assessment and performance monitoring on the implementation of the DRRM Plans.

